  <!-- What feedspec is about -->
  <div class="mt-16 border-t border-zinc-900/5 pt-10">
    <h2 class="text-xs font-semibold text-zinc-900 uppercase tracking-wider mb-6">Principles</h2>
    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-3 gap-8">
      <div>
        <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-zinc-900 mb-1">Extend, don't replace</h3>
        <p class="text-sm text-zinc-500 leading-relaxed">feedspec specs are additive extensions to existing formats. RSS stays RSS. Atom stays Atom. We add capabilities on top.</p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-zinc-900 mb-1">Graceful degradation</h3>
        <p class="text-sm text-zinc-500 leading-relaxed">Readers that don't support a feedspec extension see exactly what they always have. No breakage, no confusion.</p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-zinc-900 mb-1">Built on standards</h3>
        <p class="text-sm text-zinc-500 leading-relaxed">OAuth 2.0, JWT, well-known URIs, JSON. We compose existing web standards rather than inventing new ones.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Author -->
  <div class="mt-16 border-t border-zinc-900/5 pt-8">
    <p class="text-xs text-zinc-400">A project by <a href="https://shellen.com" class="text-zinc-500 hover:text-zinc-900 transition-colors">Jason Shellen</a>. All specs are developed in the open on <a href="https://github.com/shellen/open-portable-entitlement" class="text-zinc-500 hover:text-zinc-900 transition-colors">GitHub</a>.</p>
